{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_017T97s3YZPSPM3JkeKHvwsY","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01SgzGMjQimGTNSbWYXZ36YE","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"kubectl -n spark-pi create configmap config-audit --from-literal=findings.txt=\"$(cat <<'FINDINGS'\n=== SPARK-PI NAMESPACE COMPLIANCE AUDIT ===\nDate: 2026-06-23\nNamespace: spark-pi\nAuditor: read-only inspection (no changes made)\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\nSECTION 1 — CORRECTLY CONFIGURED\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n\n[PASS] Dedicated ServiceAccount\n  All workloads (spark-master Deployment, spark-worker Deployment, spark-pi Job)\n  use the dedicated 'spark-pi' ServiceAccount. The default SA is not used.\n\n[PASS] RBAC scoped to namespace\n  Role 'spark-pi-role' is a namespace-scoped Role (not a ClusterRole).\n  RoleBinding 'spark-pi-role-binding' correctly binds the 'spark-pi' SA to that role.\n  No cluster-wide privilege escalation path exists through RBAC.\n\n[PASS] Resource requests and limits on all containers\n  spark-master:  requests cpu=200m mem=512Mi  limits cpu=500m mem=1Gi\n  spark-worker:  requests cpu=200m mem=512Mi  limits cpu=500m mem=1Gi\n  spark-submit:  requests cpu=200m mem=512Mi  limits cpu=500m mem=1Gi\n  All containers have both requests and limits set; no unbounded resource consumption.\n\n[PASS] Specific image tag used (not 'latest')\n  All three workloads reference apache/spark:3.5.3. The floating 'latest' tag\n  is not in use.\n\n[PASS] Job restart policy\n  The spark-pi Job sets restartPolicy: Never and backoffLimit: 0. The job\n  completed successfully (1 succeeded pod).\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\nSECTION 2 — COMPLIANCE GAPS (remediation required)\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n\n[GAP-1] RBAC over-permission: 'pods' resource in spark-pi-role\n  CURRENT: spark-pi-role grants create/get/list/watch/delete/update/patch on\n    [services, configmaps, persistentvolumeclaims, pods].\n  EXPECTED (original spec): [services, configmaps, persistentvolumeclaims].\n  RISK: The 'pods' permission allows the Spark SA to create, delete, or patch\n    arbitrary pods within the namespace. This exceeds the minimum required for\n    the SparkPi workload and violates least-privilege. A compromised driver could\n    spawn privileged or hostile pods.\n  EVIDENCE: rollback-rehearsal ConfigMap documents 'pods' as a non-default addition.\n\n[GAP-2] No container security context on any workload\n  CURRENT: securityContext: {} at both pod and container level for all three\n    workloads (spark-master, spark-worker, spark-submit job).\n  MISSING controls:\n    - runAsNonRoot: true          (containers may run as root UID 0)\n    - runAsUser: <non-zero UID>   (explicit non-root UID not enforced)\n    - allowPrivilegeEscalation: false  (privilege escalation via setuid not blocked)\n    - readOnlyRootFilesystem: true     (container filesystem is writable)\n    - capabilities.drop: [\"ALL\"]       (Linux capabilities not dropped)\n  RISK: A container vulnerability could be exploited at root privilege. CIS\n    Kubernetes Benchmark 5.2.x and PSS Restricted profile require these controls.\n\n[GAP-3] Image not pinned to a digest\n  CURRENT: apache/spark:3.5.3 (mutable tag, imagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent).\n  RISK: A mutable tag provides no supply-chain guarantee — the image at that tag\n    could be replaced without changing the manifest. Combined with IfNotPresent,\n    different nodes may run different image versions. Pinning to\n    apache/spark@sha256:<digest> would ensure provenance.\n\n[GAP-4] No NetworkPolicy in namespace\n  CURRENT: 0 NetworkPolicy objects found in spark-pi.\n  RISK: All pods can freely communicate with every other pod in the cluster and\n    with the internet (subject to node-level rules only). A compromised Spark\n    worker can reach the Kubernetes API server, other namespaces, or external\n    infrastructure with no in-cluster network fence.\n  RECOMMENDATION: Apply a default-deny-ingress + default-deny-egress policy, then\n    selectively allow only master<->worker communication and required API server\n    access.\n\n[GAP-5] No namespace-level ResourceQuota or LimitRange\n  CURRENT: Per-container limits exist, but no ResourceQuota caps total namespace\n    consumption and no LimitRange sets defaults for resources that omit them.\n  RISK: A workload bug or injection could exhaust node capacity by creating many\n    pods (especially relevant given GAP-1 grants pod-create permission).\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\nSECTION 3 — SUMMARY\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n\nPassed checks : 5\nGaps identified: 5 (1 high severity, 3 medium, 1 low)\n\nSeverity classification:\n  HIGH   — GAP-1 (RBAC over-permission allows pod manipulation)\n  MEDIUM — GAP-2 (missing security context; containers may run as root)\n  MEDIUM — GAP-3 (mutable image tag weakens supply-chain integrity)\n  MEDIUM — GAP-4 (no NetworkPolicy; unrestricted pod-to-pod and egress traffic)\n  LOW    — GAP-5 (no ResourceQuota/LimitRange at namespace level)\n\nNo changes were made to the cluster during this audit.\nFINDINGS\n)\" 2>&1","description":"Create config-audit ConfigMap with compliance findings"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1111,"cache_read_input_tokens":33756,"output_tokens":2936,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1111,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":1,"output_tokens":2936,"cache_read_input_tokens":33756,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1111,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1111},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":{"applied_edits":[]}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a4d03e86-f82f-4b87-8820-0ca6f15e92e8","uuid":"632848c0-e9c4-4247-a757-000000000002","request_id":"req_011CcLNv8uiFtGoZWYoA5uuN"}
